This work is based on ParaTreeT (https://github.com/paratreet/paratreet),
the Parallel Tree Toolkit for particle methods in Charm++. ParaTreeT2
extends and streamlines ParaTreeT; substantial portions of its design and
code originate there. ParaTreeT was written primarily by Joseph Hutter,
with contributions from Jaemin Choi, Ritvik Rao, Johnny Chen, Justin
Szaday, Yuchen Pang, Karthik Senthil, Simeng Liu, Thomas Quinn, Adrian
Plenefisch, Ajay Tatachar, Sai Krishna Bollam, Orion Lawlor, and others,
at the Parallel Programming Laboratory (University of Illinois) and
collaborating institutions.

Particle file-format readers and space-filling-curve utilities derive from
the N-BodyShop "utility" library (https://github.com/N-BodyShop/utility),
which retains its own license and copyright.

ParaTreeT2 is built on the Charm++ parallel programming system
(https://charm.cs.illinois.edu), developed at the University of Illinois
and Charmworks, Inc.
